last_task_title: Fix Mock len() STARTUP FAILURES blocking 40 tests
last_task_description:
Fix the critical STARTUP FAILED error: object of type Mock has no len() at litellm_proxy_sdk.py:150 that blocks 40 tests in test_sdk_integration.py, test_sdk_e2e.py, and test_interceptor*.py.

ROOT CAUSE:
- Line 150: len(memory_router.header_patterns) called during lifespan() startup
- During TestClient initialization, memory_router.header_patterns is a Mock object
- Mock objects dont support len() operation

AFFECTED TESTS (40 errors):
- All TestHealthEndpoint tests (ERROR at setup)
- All TestMemoryRoutingInfoEndpoint tests (ERROR at setup)  
- All TestChatCompletionsNonStreaming tests (ERROR at setup)
- All TestChatCompletionsStreaming tests (ERROR at setup)
- All TestErrorHandling tests (ERROR at setup)
- All test_interceptor.py tests (ERROR at setup)
- All test_sdk_e2e.py E2E tests (ERROR at setup)

SOLUTION:
Add resilient len() check in litellm_proxy_sdk.py:150:
if hasattr(memory_router.header_patterns, __len__):
    len(memory_router.header_patterns)

FILES TO FIX:
- src/proxy/litellm_proxy_sdk.py:150

VALIDATION:
Run: poetry run pytest tests/test_sdk_integration.py -v --tb=no
Verify 0 STARTUP FAILED errors, 40 tests move from ERROR to PASSED/FAILED
